  "prompt": "Does sound travel through empty space?",
  "response": "No, sound does not travel through empty space. Sound requires a medium, such as air, water, or solid materials, to propagate. This is because sound waves are mechanical waves that rely on the vibration of particles in a medium to transmit energy. In the vacuum of space, there are not enough particles to carry these vibrations, so sound cannot travel. This is why, for example, there is no sound in outer space.",
